The 0.27% gap is not a failure of the theory. It is the *measurement* of the difference between the bare (outside) and physical (inside) perspectives. It is the correction for being inside the moiré pattern rather than observing it from outside.

Equivalently: when a photon is created (spacetime displaced), from the photon's perspective, there is no propagation through pre-existing space — the spacetime is created simultaneously. The photon's "clock" starts at the moment of creation. This is why the photon sees a different α than the bare coupling: the photon is inside the condensate and inherits the condensate's self-measurement correction.

